oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Unidentified girl
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This image of an unidentified girl is from an old photograph album found at an estate sale. The girl wore a saque coat over a dress with a hooped skirt, and rested her left hand on the back of a chair. Her braided pigtails bore ribbons.; The children in wils003, wils004, wils005, wils006 appear to have been photographed in the same studio. The chair in this image is the same as the one in wils005.
